The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques to detect and quantify watermarks on images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia), and information retrieval, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also deals with security and privacy concerns related to watermarks, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes a novel technique to quantify the visual obstructiveness of watermarks, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
